legacy.name: Xie Feng 谢锋

result.text: It’s such a pleasure to join friends online at the Hong Kong Forum on US-China Relations. The theme this year, “Change and Progress”, is highly relevant. Changes in the world, in our times and in history are unfolding in ways like never before. Meanwhile, people’s appeal for peace, development and cooperation is getting louder and louder, and their aspiration for a better life is unstoppable. There has also been a growing call for stopping the downward spiral in China-US relations. To our encouragement, under the guidance of the two Presidents and with our joint efforts, we’ve seen positive signs of a more stable China-US relationship, with a series of high-level interactions happening, dialogue mechanisms launched, and exchanges and cooperation at various levels reignited.
